\title{Warehouse Network}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Connect to warehouse machines (DGX Spark, etc.) via local network or Tailscale. Use when SSH-ing into warehouse hosts, managing Tailscale connectivity, or accessing gx10-acee.}

\subtree{
\title{Warehouse Network}
\p{Manage SSH connections to machines on the warehouse network, with Tailscale as the cross-network fallback.}

\subtree{
\title{Hosts}
\pre{\startverb
| Host | Local IP | Tailscale IP | User | Password |
|------|----------|-------------|------|----------|
| gx10-acee (DGX Spark) | 10.1.10.153 | 100.74.215.96 | a | aaaaaa |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Connection Strategy}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Same network}: SSH directly via local IP (\code{\startverb 10.1.10.x\stopverb})}
\li{\strong{Different networks}: SSH via Tailscale IP (\code{\startverb 100.x.x.x\stopverb})}
\li{\strong{If Tailscale is offline/expired}: Must access via local network first, then run \code{\startverb sudo tailscale up --force-reauth\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Connect}
\pre{\startverb
# Try Tailscale first (works across networks)
ssh a@100.74.215.96

# Fall back to local
ssh a@10.1.10.153
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Connection Workflow}
\pre{\startverb
# 1. Check if host is on Tailscale
tailscale status | grep gx10

# 2. If online (no "offline" tag), ping to verify
tailscale ping --timeout=10s gx10-acee

# 3. If offline or node key expired, SSH via local network and re-auth
ssh a@10.1.10.153
sudo tailscale up --force-reauth
# Visit the printed auth URL in browser

# 4. Connect via Tailscale once authenticated
ssh a@100.74.215.96
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Discovering New Hosts}
\p{If a host IP is uncertain, probe a range:}

\pre{\startverb
for ip in 10.1.10.{150..155}; do
  ssh -o ConnectTimeout=5 -o BatchMode=yes a@$ip "echo $ip ok" 2>&1 &
done; wait
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Notes}
\ul{
\li{DGX Spark runs Ubuntu (aarch64), NVIDIA DGX Spark Version 7.4.0}
\li{The machine has a \code{\startverb (spark-ai-env)\stopverb} conda/venv activated by default}
\li{Tailscale node keys can expire; re-auth with \code{\startverb --force-reauth\stopverb}}
\li{sudo password is the same as the login password}
}
}
}